## 12.9 Safe Tailoring System

### Purpose

Prevent false or unsupported resume claims.

### AI Must Not

* Invent companies
* Invent degrees
* Invent job titles
* Invent dates
* Invent certifications
* Invent years of experience
* Add unsupported tools as real experience
* Guarantee interviews
* Claim certainty about ATS ranking

### AI Can

* Reword existing experience
* Reorder sections
* Emphasize relevant skills
* Improve clarity
* Improve keyword alignment
* Suggest missing skills
* Ask users to confirm experience

### Change Labels

Every major AI change should be labeled:

1. Found and used
2. Reworded from existing experience
3. Needs confirmation
4. Not added because no proof was found

### Confirmation Modal

Title:
“Confirm this skill before adding”

Message:
“Docker was found in the job description but not in your master resume. Only add it if you have real experience.”

Buttons:

* “I have experience, add it”
* “Do not add”

### Acceptance Criteria

* Unsupported skills are flagged.
* User confirmation is required before adding missing skills.
* User can reject additions.
* Change log explains what was changed and why.

